DzError DzSelectionMap::addPair ( const QString &  faceGroupName,
DzNode *  node,
bool  replaceIfExists = false 
) [slot]

Adds a new face group/node mapping to the selection map.

Parameters:
faceGroupName The name of the face group that will map to the given node.
node The node that will be selected when the face group is clicked on in the viewport.
replaceIfExists If true, checks to see if the face group is already mapped, and replaces the mapped node with the given node. If false, the operation will fail if the face group is already mapped.
Returns:
DZ_NO_ERROR on success, otherwise an error code.

void DzSelectionMap::setPointer ( const DzInFile *  file,
short  sectionID,
short  pointerID,
DzBase *  ptr 
) [virtual]

Called by the framework when reading a native file. Derived classes should override this method if they ever write out pointer values to the data file. This method will be called with the sectionID and pointerID that were given when writing the file out. The passed pointer may be shared so should not be deleted.

Parameters:
file The file being loaded
sectionID The ID of the file section being read
pointerID The ID of the pointer being read.
ptr The pointer being read.

Reimplemented from DzBase.
